[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Voice consistency:** The Wednesday-evening vignette earns its position. The "thirty-one people in the waiting room ... two ambulance bays are full ... the on-call attending physician for the surge protocol just declined because they're already on a different shift tomorrow ... inpatient is at 96% capacity and has been holding the boarders the ED sent up two hours ago" framing is the recipe's clearest operational stake-setting and lands at exactly the "I have lived this exact bad shift" register. The "This scene plays out somewhere in the United States about every fifteen minutes" follow-up correctly sets the scale.
